aptisTrapsModule.name: aptisTrapsModule

revisions.description: 04/25/00, rss 1) Made the following changes to the CVX traps: OBSOLETED TRAPS | SUPERCEDED BY -----------------------------+------------------------- aptis-l2f-tunnel-start (31) | cvx-tunnel-start (53) aptis-l2f-tunnel-stop (32) | cvx-tunnel-stop (54) aptis-l2f-tunnel-reject (33) | cvx-tunnel-reject (55) 2) Changed the notation of CVX-1800 to the generic CVX.
03/20/00, ssm 1) Changed t1 references to ds1 and t3 to ds3. 2) Added VPOP id to trap cvxSessionAuthenticationFailure.

03/17/00, ssm 1) Added traps: cvxSlaveSccFileSyncFailed, cvxSlaveSccFileSyncCompleted, and cvxSlaveSccFailed. 2) Changed severities of many traps. 3) Reformatted previously added traps: encryptionNotAllowed, cvxRadiusdSessionDisc, cvxRadiusdUnknownClient, and cvxRadiusdClientAuthFailed.
02/09/00, ssm authenticationFailure trap was erroneously being referred to as generic trap # 4 (should be 5 in v2).

01/27/00, ssm Changed subid of aptisProtrapsV2 from 2 to 0. This was done so that traps can be converted from v1 to v2 and vice-versa without changing the oid of the trap. See also the v1 version of this MIB (aptis_traps.mib).
01/27/00, ssm Obsoleted trap 15 (authenticationFailure). Added traps 81 (cvxLocalAuthenticationFailure) and 82 (cvxSessionAuthenticationFailure).
01/20/00, ssm Added 5 traps: cvxSlaveSccRemoved, cvxSlaveSccInserted, cvxFailedSlaveSccRemoved, cvxCardCrashed, and cvxCardNotResponding.

01/10/00, ssm 1) Added 2 traps: cvxSlotTempWarning and cvxSlotTempNormal. 2) Replaced all tabs with spaces. 3) Minor restructuring of text. 4) Replaced MAX-ACCESS of trap variables from 'read-only' to 'accessible-for-notify'.
12/27/99, ssm Added 4 traps: cvxAuthServerRevived, cvxPrimaryDhcpServerContactFailed, cvxPrimaryDhcpServerContactRevived, and cvxSecondaryDhcpServerContactFailed.

aptisTrapsModule.contactinfo: Customer Service Department Nortel Networks Email: support@aptis.com
aptisTrapsModule.description: The following variables describe the Aptis Notifications.

aptisProtraps.name: aptisProtraps
aptisProtraps.description: This subtree contains the aptis proprietary traps.

aptisProtrapsV2.name: aptisProtrapsV2
aptisProtrapsV2.description: V2 subtree for aptis proprietary traps.

aptis_fandown.name: aptis_fandown
aptis_fandown.description: The fans on the chassis have stopped functioning. This trap is only supported on systems with the smart fan tray. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

aptis_dc1down.name: aptis_dc1down
aptis_dc1down.description: The DC1 power supply has stopped functioning. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

aptis_dc2down.name: aptis_dc2down
aptis_dc2down.description: The DC2 power supply has stopped functioning. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

aptis_ac1down.name: aptis_ac1down
aptis_ac1down.description: The AC1 power supply has stopped functioning. This trap is no longer supported.

aptis_ac2down.name: aptis_ac2down
aptis_ac2down.description: The AC2 power supply has stopped functioning. This trap is no longer supported.

aptis_acdc1down.name: aptis_acdc1down
aptis_acdc1down.description: The ACDC1 power converter has stopped functioning. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

aptis_acdc2down.name: aptis_acdc2down
aptis_acdc2down.description: The ACDC2 power converter has stopped functioning. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

aptis_acdc3down.name: aptis_acdc3down
aptis_acdc3down.description: The ACDC3 power converter has stopped functioning. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

aptis_flashmount.name: aptis_flashmount
aptis_flashmount.description: The flash card has been mounted. See also trap aptis-flashdismount. This trap carries a severity of 2 (warning).

aptis_flashdismount.name: aptis_flashdismount
aptis_flashdismount.description: The flash card has been dismounted. See also trap aptis-flashmount. This trap carries a severity of 2 (warning).

aptis_coldStart.name: aptis_coldStart
aptis_coldStart.description: A coldStart trap signifies that the sending protocol entity is reinitializing itself such that the agent's configuration or the protocol entity implementation may be altered. This trap carries a severity of 2 (warning).

warmStart.name: warmStart
warmStart.description: A warmStart trap signifies that the sending protocol entity is reinitializing itself such that neither the agent configuration nor the protocol entity implementation is altered. This trap carries a severity of 2 (warning).

linkDown.name: linkDown
linkDown.description: A linkDown trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes a failure in one of the communications links represented in the agent's configuration. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

linkUp.name: linkUp
linkUp.description: A linkUp trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes that one of the communications links represented in the agent's configuration has come up. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

authenticationFailure.name: authenticationFailure
authenticationFailure.description: An authenticationFailure trap signifies that the sending protocol entity is the addressee of a protocol message that is not properly authenticated. While implementations of the SNMP must be capable of generating this trap, they must also be capable of suppressing the emission of such traps via an implementation-specific mechanism. NOTE: This trap has been obsoleted and replaced by specific trap #s 81 (cvxLocalAuthenticationFailure) and 82 (cvxSessionAuthenticationFailure) and generic trap # 5 (authenticationFailure). This trap carries a severity of 3 (error).

aptis_radius_fail.name: aptis_radius_fail
aptis_radius_fail.description: No Radius Server is available. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

aptis_slot_up.name: aptis_slot_up
aptis_slot_up.description: Slot is up. See also trap aptis-slot-down. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

aptis_slot_down.name: aptis_slot_down
aptis_slot_down.description: Slot is down. See also trap aptis-slot-up. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

aptis_slot_cfg_chng.name: aptis_slot_cfg_chng
aptis_slot_cfg_chng.description: Slot configuration has changed. This trap carries a severity of 1 (notice).

aptis_ds1_red_alarm.name: aptis_ds1_red_alarm
aptis_ds1_red_alarm.description: The specified DS1 is in red alarm. See also trap aptis-ds1-alarm-clear. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

aptis_ds1_yellow_alarm.name: aptis_ds1_yellow_alarm
aptis_ds1_yellow_alarm.description: The specified DS1 is in yellow alarm. See also trap aptis-ds1-alarm-clear. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

aptis_ds1_alarm_clear.name: aptis_ds1_alarm_clear
aptis_ds1_alarm_clear.description: The specified DS1 is no longer in alarm. See also traps aptis-ds1-red-alarm and aptis-ds1-yellow-alarm. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

aptis_ds3_red_alarm.name: aptis_ds3_red_alarm
aptis_ds3_red_alarm.description: The specified DS3 is in red alarm. See also trap aptis-ds3-alarm-clear. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

aptis_ds3_yellow_alarm.name: aptis_ds3_yellow_alarm
aptis_ds3_yellow_alarm.description: The specified DS3 is in yellow alarm. See also trap aptis-ds3-alarm-clear. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

aptis_ds3_alarm_clear.name: aptis_ds3_alarm_clear
aptis_ds3_alarm_clear.description: The specified DS3 is no longer in alarm. See also traps aptis-ds3-red-alarm and aptis-ds3-yellow-alarm. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

aptis_isdn_link_up.name: aptis_isdn_link_up
aptis_isdn_link_up.description: The specified ISDN data link is up. See also trap aptis-isdn-link-down. This trap carries a severity of 3 (error).

aptis_isdn_link_down.name: aptis_isdn_link_down
aptis_isdn_link_down.description: The specified ISDN data link is down. See also trap aptis-isdn-link-up. This trap carries a severity of 3 (error).

aptis_isdn_link_reset.name: aptis_isdn_link_reset
aptis_isdn_link_reset.description: The specified ISDN data link has been reset by the switch. This trap carries a severity of 3 (error).

aptis_temp_exceeded.name: aptis_temp_exceeded
aptis_temp_exceeded.description: The card in the specified slot has exceeded its safe operational temperature and is being shut down. See also traps cvxSlotTempWarning and cvxSlotTempNormal. This trap carries a severity of 7 (fatal).

aptis_cvx_ss7_gateway_failover.name: aptis_cvx_ss7_gateway_failover
aptis_cvx_ss7_gateway_failover.description: The CVX has failed over to the next CVX-SS7 Gateway. This trap carries a severity of 2 (warning).

aptis_l2f_tunnel_start.name: aptis_l2f_tunnel_start
aptis_l2f_tunnel_start.description: The CVX has successfully opened an L2F tunnel. See also trap aptis-l2f-tunnel-stop. This trap carries a severity of 1 (notice). This trap has been replaced by cvx-tunnel-start, {aptisProtrapsV2 53}.

aptis_l2f_tunnel_stop.name: aptis_l2f_tunnel_stop
aptis_l2f_tunnel_stop.description: The CVX has closed an L2F tunnel that had been opened successfully. See also trap aptis-l2f-tunnel-start. This trap carries a severity of 1 (notice). This trap has been replaced by cvx-tunnel-stop, {aptisProtrapsV2 54}.

aptis_l2f_tunnel_reject.name: aptis_l2f_tunnel_reject
aptis_l2f_tunnel_reject.description: The CVX has failed to open an L2F tunnel. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert). This trap has been replaced by cvx-tunnel-reject, {aptisProtrapsV2 55}.

cvx_MAC_modems_below_threshold.name: cvx_MAC_modems_below_threshold
cvx_MAC_modems_below_threshold.description: The percent of functioning modems on the specified MAC board has gone below the defined threshold. See also trap cvx-MAC-modems-above-threshold. This trap carries a severity of 4 (critical).

cvx_MAC_modems_above_threshold.name: cvx_MAC_modems_above_threshold
cvx_MAC_modems_above_threshold.description: The percent of functioning modems on the specified MAC board has gone above or equal to the defined threshold. See also trap cvx-MAC-modems-below-threshold. This trap carries a severity of 4 (critical).

cvx_total_modems_below_threshold.name: cvx_total_modems_below_threshold
cvx_total_modems_below_threshold.description: The percent of functioning modems on the CVX has fallen below the defined threshold. See also trap cvx-total-modems-above-threshold. This trap carries a severity of 4 (critical).

cvx_total_modems_above_threshold.name: cvx_total_modems_above_threshold
cvx_total_modems_above_threshold.description: The percent of functioning modems on the CVX is now equal to or above the defined threshold. See also trap cvx-total-modems-below-threshold. This trap carries a severity of 4 (critical).

cvx_local_pswd_change.name: cvx_local_pswd_change
cvx_local_pswd_change.description: The local password on the CVX has been modified. This trap carries a severity of 1 (notice).

cvx_auth_server_failover.name: cvx_auth_server_failover
cvx_auth_server_failover.description: The most recently used authentication server cannot be contacted. The primary contact has been switched to the server indicated. See also trap cvxAuthServerRevived. This trap carries a severity of 2 (warning).

cvx_acct_server_failure.name: cvx_acct_server_failure
cvx_acct_server_failure.description: Communication has been lost with all configured accounting servers. The address indicated in the trap is the last address tried. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

cvx_acct_server_failover.name: cvx_acct_server_failover
cvx_acct_server_failover.description: The most recently used accounting server cannot be contacted. The primary contact has been switched to the server indicated. This trap carries a severity of 2 (warning).

cvx_ss7_gateway_down.name: cvx_ss7_gateway_down
cvx_ss7_gateway_down.description: Communication has been lost with the ss7 gateway indicated. See also trap cvx-ss7-gateway-up. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

cvx_ss7_gateway_up.name: cvx_ss7_gateway_up
cvx_ss7_gateway_up.description: Communication has been established with the ss7 gateway indicated. See also trap cvx-ss7-gateway-down. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

cvx_Ds3_failover.name: cvx_Ds3_failover
cvx_Ds3_failover.description: The primary DS3 in the indicated slot has failed and the secondary has resumed responsibility. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

cvx_Scc_failover.name: cvx_Scc_failover
cvx_Scc_failover.description: The primary SCC in the indicated slot has failed and the secondary has resumed operation. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

cvx_ethernet_port_up.name: cvx_ethernet_port_up
cvx_ethernet_port_up.description: The specified Ethernet Port is initialized. This trap will occur at boot time and when an ethernet port is reinitialized after a cvx-ethernet-port-down trap. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

cvx_ethernet_port_down.name: cvx_ethernet_port_down
cvx_ethernet_port_down.description: The specified Ethernet port has failed. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

cvx_Hssi_port_up.name: cvx_Hssi_port_up
cvx_Hssi_port_up.description: The specified HSSI Port is initialized. This trap will occur at boot time and when an HSSI port is reinitialized after a cvx-hssi-port-down trap. This trap carries a severity of 7 (fatal).

cvx_Hssi_port_down.name: cvx_Hssi_port_down
cvx_Hssi_port_down.description: The specified HSSI port has failed. This trap carries a severity of 7 (fatal).

cvx_local_auth_failure_threshold_exceede.name: cvx_local_auth_failure_threshold_exceeded
cvx_local_auth_failure_threshold_exceede.description: A consecutive number of local authorization failures has exceeded the noted threshold. The trap contains the number of consecutive failed attempts and additional information on the client host (an IP Address for FTP, or session number for telnet connections). This trap carries a severity of 2 (warning).

cvx_preAuth_fail.name: cvx_preAuth_fail
cvx_preAuth_fail.description: No pre-authorization server is available. The IP address shows the last server tried. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

cvx_auth_fail.name: cvx_auth_fail
cvx_auth_fail.description: No authorization server is available. The IP address shows the last server tried. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

cvx_tunnel_start.name: cvx_tunnel_start
cvx_tunnel_start.description: The CVX has successfully opened a tunnel. This trap carries a severity of 1 (notice).

cvx_tunnel_stop.name: cvx_tunnel_stop
cvx_tunnel_stop.description: The CVX has closed a tunnel that had been opened successfully. This trap carries a severity of 1 (notice).

cvx_tunnel_reject.name: cvx_tunnel_reject
cvx_tunnel_reject.description: The CVX has failed to open a tunnel. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

cvx_radius_packet_discard.name: cvx_radius_packet_discard
cvx_radius_packet_discard.description: A radius response packet was discarded. This trap carries a severity of 3 (error).

cvx_fanup.name: cvx_fanup
cvx_fanup.description: The fans on the chassis have resumed functioning. This trap is only supported on systems with the smart fan tray. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

cvx_dc1up.name: cvx_dc1up
cvx_dc1up.description: The DC1 power supply has resumed functioning. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

cvx_dc2up.name: cvx_dc2up
cvx_dc2up.description: The DC2 power supply has resumed functioning. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

cvx_acdc1up.name: cvx_acdc1up
cvx_acdc1up.description: The ACDC1 power converter has resumed functioning. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

cvx_acdc2up.name: cvx_acdc2up
cvx_acdc2up.description: The ACDC2 power converter has resumed functioning. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

cvx_acdc3up.name: cvx_acdc3up
cvx_acdc3up.description: The ACDC3 power converter has resumed functioning. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

cvx_filter_error.name: cvx_filter_error
cvx_filter_error.description: A Filter-Id attribute containing an unknown filter name was received from a radius server. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

cvx_slave_flash_missing.name: cvx_slave_flash_missing
cvx_slave_flash_missing.description: No flash card has been detected on the slave SCC (System Control Card) unit. See also trap cvxSlaveSccFlashDetected. This trap carries a severity of 3 (error).

cvxSlaveSccFlashDetected.name: cvxSlaveSccFlashDetected
cvxSlaveSccFlashDetected.description: The flash card has been detected on the slave SCC (System Control Card) unit. NOTE: This trap is only sent if the complementary trap cvx-slave-flash-missing was sent previously. This trap carries a severity of 3 (error).

cvxAuthServerRevived.name: cvxAuthServerRevived
cvxAuthServerRevived.description: The authentication server identified by trapIpAddr that had previously failed has been revived. The server is identified by trapIpAddr. See also notification cvx-auth-server-failover. This trap carries a severity of 1 (notice).

cvxPrimaryDhcpServerContactFailed.name: cvxPrimaryDhcpServerContactFailed
cvxPrimaryDhcpServerContactFailed.description: Failed to establish contact with the primary DHCP server identified by trapIpAddr. If a secondary DHCP server has been configured, it will be tried next. NOTE: Every time a new request is received to obtain an IP address via DHCP, the primary DHCP server is always tried first (even though previous attempts to contact it may have failed). See also trap cvxPrimaryDhcpServerContactRevived. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

cvxPrimaryDhcpServerContactRevived.name: cvxPrimaryDhcpServerContactRevived
cvxPrimaryDhcpServerContactRevived.description: Contact has been reestablished with the primary DHCP server identified by trapIpAddr. NOTE: Every time a new request is received to obtain an IP address via DHCP, the primary DHCP server is always tried first (even though previous attempts to contact it may have failed). See also trap cvxPrimaryDhcpServerContactFail. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

cvxSecondaryDhcpServerContactFailed.name: cvxSecondaryDhcpServerContactFailed
cvxSecondaryDhcpServerContactFailed.description: Failed to establish contact with the secondary (backup) DHCP server identified by trapIpAddr. Note that no trap is issued when contact is reestablished with the secondary DHCP server. This trap carries a severity of 5 (alert).

cvxSlotTempWarning.name: cvxSlotTempWarning
cvxSlotTempWarning.description: Slot temperature has exceeded the configured warning level. If the slot temperature exceeds the configured threshold limit, the card in the slot will be shut down. trapSlotNum identifies the affected slot. trapTempCurrent specifies the current temperature and trapTempConfigWarningLevel specifies the configured warning level (both in degrees Celsius). See also traps cvxSlotTempNormal and aptis-temp-exceeded. This trap carries a severity of 4 (critical).

cvxSlotTempNormal.name: cvxSlotTempNormal
cvxSlotTempNormal.description: Slot temperature is back to normal (below the configured warning level). trapSlotNum identifies the affected slot. trapTempCurrent specifies the current temperature and trapTempConfigWarningLevel specifies the configured warning level (both in degrees Celsius). See also traps cvxSlotTempWarning and aptis-temp-exceeded. This trap carries a severity of 4 (critical).

cvxSlaveSccRemoved.name: cvxSlaveSccRemoved
cvxSlaveSccRemoved.description: The master SCC (System Control Card) has detected that the slave SCC has been removed from the system. File synchronization will cease. See also traps cvxSlaveSccInserted and cvxFailedSlaveSccRemoved. This trap carries a severity of 3 (error).

cvxSlaveSccInserted.name: cvxSlaveSccInserted
cvxSlaveSccInserted.description: The master SCC (System Control Card) has detected that the slave SCC has been inserted into the system. File synchronization will start or resume. See also traps cvxSlaveSccRemoved and cvxFailedSlaveSccRemoved. This trap carries a severity of 3 (error).

cvxFailedSlaveSccRemoved.name: cvxFailedSlaveSccRemoved
cvxFailedSlaveSccRemoved.description: The master SCC (System Control Card) has detected that the slave SCC that had previously failed has been removed from the system. See also traps cvxSlaveSccRemoved and cvxSlaveSccInserted. This trap carries a severity of 3 (error).

cvxCardCrashed.name: cvxCardCrashed
cvxCardCrashed.description: The card in slot trapSlotNum has crashed. The crash block has been written to the flash card. A restart of the card will be attempted. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

cvxCardNotResponding.name: cvxCardNotResponding
cvxCardNotResponding.description: The card in slot trapSlotNum is not responding to the system watchdog. A restart of the card will be attempted. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

cvxLocalAuthenticationFailure.name: cvxLocalAuthenticationFailure
cvxLocalAuthenticationFailure.description: This trap is generated when a user fails the local authentication process while trying to log into the CVX shell service. Local authentication is performed via a unix-like username/password sequence. The username associated with the login is contained in the variable trapUserName. A sufficient number of local authentication failures can trigger the trap cvx-local-auth-failure-threshold-exceeded. For an authentication failure related to the authentication of received SNMP packets, the generic trap authenticationFailure (generic trap # 5) is used. NOTE: The previously defined enterprise-specific trap called authenticationFailure (specific trap # 15) that used to cover all kinds of authentication failures has been obsoleted and replaced by this trap, trap cvxSessionAuthenticationFailure, and generic trap authenticationFailure (generic trap # 5). This trap carries a severity of 1 (notice).

cvxSessionAuthenticationFailure.name: cvxSessionAuthenticationFailure
cvxSessionAuthenticationFailure.description: This trap is generated when an authentication failure occurs during session setup. The session id number associated with the session is contained in the variable trapSessionId. If there is an associated VPOP id, it is returned in the variable trapVpopId. The types of sessions for which this trap can be issued are: atmp, tcp, dvs, fax, ppp, rlogin, telnet, and voip. For an authentication failure related to the authentication of received SNMP packets, the generic trap authenticationFailure (generic trap # 5) is used. NOTE: The previously defined enterprise-specific trap called authenticationFailure (specific trap # 15) that used to cover all kinds of authentication failures has been obsoleted and replaced by this trap, trap cvxLocalAuthenticationFailure, and generic trap authenticationFailure (generic trap # 5). This trap carries a severity of 1 (notice).

encryptionNotAllowed.name: encryptionNotAllowed
encryptionNotAllowed.description: Encryption operations cannot be performed if the SCC I board is present. Encryption is only supported on a SCC II board that has a VMS120 chip for encryption acceleration. Also, even if the VMS120 chip is present, it may not have encrypting functionality turned on in the hardware. The encryption may also have been disabled via configuration. This trap has a high severity because none of the packets protected by the IPSec encryption may now be received or sent by the CVX. This trap carries a severity of 6 (emergency).

cvxRadiusdSessionDisc.name: cvxRadiusdSessionDisc
cvxRadiusdSessionDisc.description: A Disconnect-Request received from the RADIUS client with IP address trapIpAddr resulted in termination of one or more sessions. This trap carries a severity of 0 (info).

cvxRadiusdUnknownClient.name: cvxRadiusdUnknownClient
cvxRadiusdUnknownClient.description: A Disconnect-Request was received from an unknown RADIUS client with IP address trapIpAddr. This trap carries a severity of 0 (info).

cvxRadiusdClientAuthFailed.name: cvxRadiusdClientAuthFailed
cvxRadiusdClientAuthFailed.description: A Disconnect-Request received from the RADIUS client with IP address trapIpAddr failed authentication. This trap carries a severity of 0 (info).

cvxSlaveSccFileSyncFailed.name: cvxSlaveSccFileSyncFailed
cvxSlaveSccFileSyncFailed.description: The master SCC (System Control Card) detected error(s) while performing file synchronization with the slave SCC. This trap carries a severity of 4 (critical).

cvxSlaveSccFileSyncCompleted.name: cvxSlaveSccFileSyncCompleted
cvxSlaveSccFileSyncCompleted.description: The master SCC (System Control Card) successfully completed file synchronization with the slave SCC. This trap carries a severity of 1 (notice).

cvxSlaveSccFailed.name: cvxSlaveSccFailed
cvxSlaveSccFailed.description: The master SCC (System Control Card) has detected that the slave SCC has failed. File synchronization will cease. See also related trap cvxFailedSlaveSccRemoved. This trap carries a severity of 7 (fatal).

trapGenNum.name: trapGenNum
trapGenNum.description: A unigue incrementing integer assigned for each trap.

trapPath.name: trapPath
trapPath.description: A path string to the object associated with the trap.

trapSeverity.name: trapSeverity
trapSeverity.description: The severity of this trap, 7 being most severe.

trapString.name: trapString
trapString.description: Extra text associated with the trap.

trapIpAddr.name: trapIpAddr
trapIpAddr.description: An IP address associated with the trap.

trapSlotNum.name: trapSlotNum
trapSlotNum.description: A slot number associated with the trap.

trapPortNum.name: trapPortNum
trapPortNum.description: A port number associated with the trap.

trapTunnelType.name: trapTunnelType
trapTunnelType.description: A tunnel type associated with the trap.

trapUserName.name: trapUserName
trapUserName.description: The user name assiciated with this trap.

trapAuthThreshold.name: trapAuthThreshold
trapAuthThreshold.description: The number of consecutive authorization failures.

trapFilterName.name: trapFilterName
trapFilterName.description: The filter name assiciated with this trap.

trapTempConfigWarningLevel.name: trapTempConfigWarningLevel
trapTempConfigWarningLevel.description: Configured warning level temperature in degrees Celsius.

trapSessionId.name: trapSessionId
trapSessionId.description: A session id number associated with the trap.

trapVpopId.name: trapVpopId
trapVpopId.description: A VPOP (Virtual Point of Presence) id associated with the trap.
